13. Category / Budget Entity — Enum Type Fix Added @JdbcTypeCode(SqlTypes.NAMED_ENUM) alongside @Enumerated(EnumType
    .STRING) on the type, predefinedCategory, and period enum fields. This was needed because PostgreSQL treats custom enum
    types (category_type, predefined_category, budget_period) as distinct types and refuses to accept a plain string —
    Hibernate was binding them as character varying by default, causing an insert failure.
